WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:04.296 --> 00:00:05.297
[inhales sharply]

2
00:00:06.757 --> 00:00:09.634
[sighs] Shit. I'm fading.

3
00:00:09.635 --> 00:00:11.969
Yeah. me too.
Maybe put on some music for us.

4
00:00:11.970 --> 00:00:13.971
- [button clicking]
- [radio presenters speaking]

5
00:00:13.972 --> 00:00:16.682
["Lost Highway" playing on radio]

6
00:00:16.683 --> 00:00:17.684
[chuckles]

7
00:00:20.687 --> 00:00:24.357
<i>♪ I'm a rolling stone ♪</i>

8
00:00:24.358 --> 00:00:26.026
- Wait. where's Dad?
- Hmm?

9
00:00:26.652 --> 00:00:28.612
Dad. He was right behind us.

10
00:00:30.197 --> 00:00:32.240
[gasps] Mom! Hannah! Stop! Stop!

11
00:00:32.241 --> 00:00:34.493
[gasps. breathing heavily]

12
00:00:36.161 --> 00:00:37.621
Hey. you have a good nap?

13
00:00:38.497 --> 00:00:42.583
I... didn't mean to doze off. Sorry.

14
00:00:42.584 --> 00:00:45.546
It's okay. You needed it. Want a chip?

15
00:00:47.714 --> 00:00:48.799
No. thanks.

16
00:00:49.716 --> 00:00:50.843
Are we late?

17
00:00:51.426 --> 00:00:53.636
No. no.
Dad took the fast lane a while back.

18
00:00:53.637 --> 00:00:56.138
He's gonna catch Grady and they'll...
they'll wait for us.

19
00:00:56.139 --> 00:00:58.433
You used the new burners. right?

20
00:01:01.979 --> 00:01:04.021
Look. I-I'm sorry I called Shep.

21
00:01:04.022 --> 00:01:05.858
Oh. don't be. You didn't know.

22
00:01:07.025 --> 00:01:08.026
Yeah.

23
00:01:08.986 --> 00:01:10.903
Course. if I'd known
you were that into Shep...

24
00:01:10.904 --> 00:01:13.322
- [scoffs] I'm not that into Shep.
- I mean. we've been gone. what?

25
00:01:13.323 --> 00:01:15.116
Three days? I'm just saying...

26
00:01:15.117 --> 00:01:16.285
Well. you can stop.

27
00:01:21.456 --> 00:01:22.541
No. but. seriously.

28
00:01:23.876 --> 00:01:25.251
don't feel bad.

29
00:01:25.252 --> 00:01:28.421
It's hard being cut off from everyone.

30
00:01:28.422 --> 00:01:29.631
It's really hard.

31
00:01:30.591 --> 00:01:31.675
Yeah.

32
00:01:34.052 --> 00:01:35.220
[sighs]

33
00:01:37.000 --> 00:01:43.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

34
00:03:06.186 --> 00:03:07.437
[line ringing]

35
00:03:08.480 --> 00:03:11.358
<i>Hey. you've reached Grady Bradford.
Leave a message.</i>

36
00:03:12.985 --> 00:03:14.068
[line clicks]

37
00:03:14.069 --> 00:03:15.778
[line ringing]

38
00:03:15.779 --> 00:03:16.988
[Owen on phone] <i>Grady's not here.</i>

39
00:03:16.989 --> 00:03:19.073
<i>He's never missed a meeting
without giving me a heads-up.</i>

40
00:03:19.074 --> 00:03:20.575
[Hannah on phone]
<i>Maybe we should go to his office.</i>

41
00:03:20.576 --> 00:03:22.368
[Owen] <i>We can't go
to the Marshals Service.</i>

42
00:03:22.369 --> 00:03:23.953
[Hannah] <i>You can't. I can.</i>

43
00:03:23.954 --> 00:03:27.081
[Owen] <i>I don't like it. If the Campanos
do have some kind of a mole...</i>

44
00:03:27.082 --> 00:03:30.251
[Hannah] <i>If anything feels off.
I'll leave as quickly as I came.</i>

45
00:03:30.252 --> 00:03:33.088
[Owen] <i>Okay. fine. Just be careful.</i>

46
00:03:37.968 --> 00:03:39.177
Okay.

47
00:03:39.178 --> 00:03:42.054
Go for a drive.
I'll be back in half an hour.

48
00:03:42.055 --> 00:03:43.764
Maybe I'll grab a drink at The Never Dry.

49
00:03:43.765 --> 00:03:45.266
- [sighs] Bailey.
- I know. I'll be careful.

50
00:03:45.267 --> 00:03:46.602
But you too. okay?

51
00:04:04.828 --> 00:04:06.830
[suspenseful music playing]

52
00:04:08.957 --> 00:04:11.250
[secretary] You said you were here
to see Agent Bradford?

53
00:04:11.251 --> 00:04:12.252
Yes.

54
00:04:12.836 --> 00:04:14.171
Is he not in?

55
00:04:15.088 --> 00:04:16.172
Who's asking?

56
00:04:16.173 --> 00:04:18.341
Tell him it's an old friend.

57
00:04:38.320 --> 00:04:39.446
This way. ma'am.

58
00:04:39.947 --> 00:04:40.948
[Hannah] Yeah.

59
00:04:54.628 --> 00:04:56.963
Maybe I'll just come back another time.

60
00:04:56.964 --> 00:05:00.050
Miss Hall. we didn't have the pleasure
the last time you were in Austin.

61
00:05:00.592 --> 00:05:03.094
Maris Anderson. What can I do for you?

62
00:05:03.095 --> 00:05:04.972
Miss Anderson. Grady's mentioned you.

63
00:05:05.472 --> 00:05:07.182
Is Grady here today?

64
00:05:07.683 --> 00:05:09.892
Did Agent Bradford say he would be here?

65
00:05:09.893 --> 00:05:12.479
No. but I need to speak with him.

66
00:05:13.146 --> 00:05:14.982
Well. I'm his boss. How can I help?

67
00:05:20.153 --> 00:05:21.280
Maybe I should go.

68
00:05:22.155 --> 00:05:23.156
Miss Hall.

69
00:05:23.866 --> 00:05:26.952
I'm the US Marshal
for the Western District of Texas.

70
00:05:27.494 --> 00:05:31.206
I'm a sworn officer of the law
and across every case in this office.

71
00:05:32.165 --> 00:05:34.376
If there's something wrong.
I'd like to help.

72
00:05:38.297 --> 00:05:40.757
Is there somewhere
we could speak privately?

73
00:05:45.971 --> 00:05:46.972
[Maris] Better?

74
00:05:48.098 --> 00:05:49.099
Yes. thank you.

75
00:05:51.643 --> 00:05:52.686
Now...

76
00:05:54.897 --> 00:05:56.272
tell me what's going on.

77
00:05:56.273 --> 00:05:59.066
It's about the Campano case.

78
00:05:59.067 --> 00:06:00.360
Which Campano case?

79
00:06:01.361 --> 00:06:04.197
The case Grady is working
with AUSA Fisher?

80
00:06:04.198 --> 00:06:05.324
I know it's on the Q.T.

81
00:06:06.283 --> 00:06:07.366
This is Delia Fisher?

82
00:06:07.367 --> 00:06:10.620
Yes. in the US Attorney's Office. I was
told Grady was keeping you in the loop...

83
00:06:10.621 --> 00:06:13.248
- [phone beeps]
- Rochelle. do you have Grady yet?

84
00:06:13.874 --> 00:06:15.500
[Rochelle] <i>He's not answering his phone.</i>

85
00:06:15.501 --> 00:06:17.044
- Keep trying.
- [phone beeps]

86
00:06:18.629 --> 00:06:22.049
- You're not in the loop. are you?
- Which loop exactly would that be?

87
00:06:22.716 --> 00:06:24.175
I'm just gonna call him.

88
00:06:24.176 --> 00:06:27.345
Miss Hall. I can tell that
you don't entirely trust me.

89
00:06:27.346 --> 00:06:28.971
But the last time I checked.

90
00:06:28.972 --> 00:06:32.600
the FBI was running a few investigations
into the Campanos.

91
00:06:32.601 --> 00:06:35.521
And as far as I know.
Grady wasn't involved in any of them.

92
00:06:36.313 --> 00:06:39.398
So. unless you want me
to start making calls all over town.

93
00:06:39.399 --> 00:06:42.778
I'm gonna need you to sit back down
and start from the beginning.

94
00:06:49.618 --> 00:06:50.786
Conference room.

95
00:06:51.995 --> 00:06:53.247
Now. people!

96
00:06:54.831 --> 00:06:56.124
Shut the door.

97
00:06:57.042 --> 00:06:58.709
When's the last time you talked to Grady?

98
00:06:58.710 --> 00:07:00.419
- I haven't.
- Ed?

99
00:07:00.420 --> 00:07:02.630
No. I... no. Nope.

100
00:07:02.631 --> 00:07:06.759
And he doesn't have you guys
working on anything extracurricular?

101
00:07:06.760 --> 00:07:08.636
I'm not working on anything with him.

102
00:07:08.637 --> 00:07:09.971
- [phone beeps]
- Rochelle?

103
00:07:09.972 --> 00:07:11.097
[Rochelle] <i>Yes. ma'am.</i>

104
00:07:11.098 --> 00:07:12.599
Get me the US Attorney's Office.

105
00:07:18.480 --> 00:07:21.440
I'm sorry to be so cloak-and-dagger.

106
00:07:21.441 --> 00:07:24.360
but we have some real security concerns.

107
00:07:24.361 --> 00:07:27.238
I'm hoping you'll be discreet.

108
00:07:27.239 --> 00:07:29.615
- [phone beeps]
- Delia. I've got Hannah Hall.

109
00:07:29.616 --> 00:07:31.909
Could you tell her what you told me?

110
00:07:31.910 --> 00:07:34.287
Hi. Hannah. This is Delia Fisher
in the US Attorney's Office.

111
00:07:34.288 --> 00:07:36.706
- You're working with Grady?
- <i>Right. So. that's the thing.</i>

112
00:07:36.707 --> 00:07:39.292
<i>Grady and I were discussing a case
against the Campanos.</i>

113
00:07:39.293 --> 00:07:41.253
but it was... it was very much
in the theoretical stage.

114
00:07:42.421 --> 00:07:43.714
What do you mean theoretical?

115
00:07:44.590 --> 00:07:46.132
<i>I mean. he told me</i>

116
00:07:46.133 --> 00:07:48.759
he thought they'd gotten involved
with an international criminal syndicate.

117
00:07:48.760 --> 00:07:51.012
And I told him what proof
I would need to prosecute.

118
00:07:51.013 --> 00:07:52.806
But that's...
that's really as far as it went.

119
00:07:53.432 --> 00:07:56.434
<i>I also told him if this went any further.
I'd have to loop in my boss.</i>

120
00:07:56.435 --> 00:07:58.395
<i>But that was the last I heard from him.</i>

121
00:08:00.189 --> 00:08:01.355
This was how long ago?

122
00:08:01.356 --> 00:08:03.316
<i>I'm not sure. Six weeks ago.</i>

123
00:08:03.317 --> 00:08:05.902
- <i>It was before he went on leave.</i>
- Grady's on leave?

124
00:08:05.903 --> 00:08:08.905
- Thanks. Delia. I'll take it from here.
- When did Grady go on leave?

125
00:08:08.906 --> 00:08:10.907
About a month ago.
I asked him to take some time off.

126
00:08:10.908 --> 00:08:12.575
- Why?
- Personnel matters are confidential.

127
00:08:12.576 --> 00:08:14.995
Please. We are
really counting on him. Please.

128
00:08:18.457 --> 00:08:19.791
[sighs]

129
00:08:20.459 --> 00:08:21.960
- Confidentially...
- Mm-hmm.

130
00:08:22.753 --> 00:08:24.879
...he's had a streak of bad luck.

131
00:08:24.880 --> 00:08:27.381
Deaths in three different cases.
One was a kid.

132
00:08:27.382 --> 00:08:30.134
- [sighs]
- Not his fault. but it hit him hard.

133
00:08:30.135 --> 00:08:32.803
Started taking unnecessary risks.
ignoring procedure.

134
00:08:32.804 --> 00:08:35.557
So. I told him to take some time.
get his head straight.

135
00:08:38.644 --> 00:08:39.936
All of this is new to you?

136
00:08:39.937 --> 00:08:40.938
It is.

137
00:08:41.980 --> 00:08:45.609
Grady was supposed to have
a meeting on our case yesterday.

138
00:08:49.488 --> 00:08:52.658
We haven't heard from him.
He hasn't been answering his phone.

139
00:08:54.034 --> 00:08:57.371
- [phone beeps]
- Ed. could you join us in my office?

140
00:08:58.163 --> 00:08:59.247
[Hannah] You're worried.

141
00:08:59.248 --> 00:09:01.707
[chuckles] Well.
I certainly didn't put him on leave

142
00:09:01.708 --> 00:09:04.962
to run extralegal. off-book ops
on a high-profile target. so...

143
00:09:05.462 --> 00:09:07.880
- Hey. [sighs]
- Let's run a wellness check on Grady.

144
00:09:07.881 --> 00:09:10.383
- And notify Austin PD.
- On it.

145
00:09:10.384 --> 00:09:11.592
[Hannah] I should go too.

146
00:09:11.593 --> 00:09:14.804
I'd rather you stay
until we get a beat on Grady.

147
00:09:14.805 --> 00:09:16.556
- It's safer.
- Then what?

148
00:09:16.557 --> 00:09:18.474
I honestly don't know. [sighs]

149
00:09:18.475 --> 00:09:22.019
But it sure seems like you should consider
a petition to Witness Protection.

150
00:09:22.020 --> 00:09:25.356
No. That's not for... No.
We are not there yet.

151
00:09:25.357 --> 00:09:27.733
You have been on the run
for the last four days

152
00:09:27.734 --> 00:09:28.985
and I'm missing an agent.

153
00:09:28.986 --> 00:09:30.404
I wouldn't be so sure.

154
00:09:34.825 --> 00:09:36.118
What?

155
00:09:36.618 --> 00:09:37.911
Wh-What is it?

156
00:09:39.997 --> 00:09:41.539
- [sighs]
- Hannah.

157
00:09:41.540 --> 00:09:42.749
[Hannah] Let's go.

158
00:09:54.344 --> 00:09:55.595
He's on leave?

159
00:09:55.596 --> 00:09:59.015
Are we really surprised? I mean.
we told you what he was like at the motel.

160
00:09:59.016 --> 00:10:00.308
You spoke to Delia Fisher?

161
00:10:00.309 --> 00:10:02.018
Grady hasn't spoken to her
in over a month.

162
00:10:02.019 --> 00:10:03.978
She said the case is entirely theoretical.

163
00:10:03.979 --> 00:10:05.354
But there's evidence.

164
00:10:05.355 --> 00:10:06.939
Okay. well. she doesn't have it.

165
00:10:06.940 --> 00:10:09.151
But Grady does. Or at least he did.

166
00:10:10.027 --> 00:10:11.360
- I need to go to his house.
- Uh-uh.

167
00:10:11.361 --> 00:10:13.738
They're sending Austin PD
to run a wellness check.

168
00:10:13.739 --> 00:10:16.324
It's all the more reason
why we need to get there before they do.

169
00:10:16.325 --> 00:10:17.700
Okay. we'll all go.

170
00:10:17.701 --> 00:10:20.161
[scoffs] Well. that's an unnecessary risk.

171
00:10:20.162 --> 00:10:22.872
I trusted you. now I...
I'm asking you to trust me.

172
00:10:22.873 --> 00:10:24.833
I've been to his house.
I know the neighborhood.

173
00:10:25.918 --> 00:10:27.335
He's probably right on this one.

174
00:10:27.336 --> 00:10:28.628
Okay. Fine.

175
00:10:28.629 --> 00:10:30.630
Good. And. uh... And you guys lie low.

176
00:10:30.631 --> 00:10:33.508
And if for any reason
you don't feel safe. just get out of town.

177
00:10:33.509 --> 00:10:34.800
I'll know where to find you.

178
00:10:34.801 --> 00:10:37.386
Okay. Don't die. Please.

179
00:10:37.387 --> 00:10:39.430
Not before I force us all
to go to family therapy.

180
00:10:39.431 --> 00:10:41.016
[chuckles] God forbid.

181
00:10:42.768 --> 00:10:43.936
I love you.

182
00:10:53.904 --> 00:10:55.113
[sighs]

183
00:10:55.614 --> 00:10:56.948
He's been gone for five years.

184
00:10:56.949 --> 00:10:59.368
you'd think I'd be okay
with him being away for five minutes.

185
00:11:00.869 --> 00:11:02.454
[sighs] We'll see him soon.

186
00:11:04.289 --> 00:11:05.414
We'll see him soon.

187
00:11:05.415 --> 00:11:08.377
[footsteps approaching]

188
00:11:08.961 --> 00:11:12.172
Miss Hall. can I talk to you?
Grady Bradford sent me.

189
00:11:16.134 --> 00:11:18.637
If I give you the signal.
start the engine.

190
00:11:22.307 --> 00:11:23.641
[breathing heavily]

191
00:11:23.642 --> 00:11:24.976
Can I help you?

192
00:11:24.977 --> 00:11:27.562
Relax. As long as you do what I say.
no one gets hurt.

193
00:11:27.563 --> 00:11:28.772
- [engine starts]
- Okay?

194
00:11:29.356 --> 00:11:31.400
[grunting]

195
00:11:32.276 --> 00:11:34.361
- [associate] That's enough.
- [gasps. panting]

196
00:11:37.239 --> 00:11:38.656
You gonna go quietly now?

197
00:11:38.657 --> 00:11:40.867
- [person] Hey. punk.
- [grunts]

198
00:11:40.868 --> 00:11:42.995
- [exclaims] Oh!
- [person 2] Charlie. I got 'em.

199
00:11:43.745 --> 00:11:45.621
- It's okay.
- [Charlie on phone] <i>Bailey. Hannah?</i>

200
00:11:45.622 --> 00:11:47.040
<i>Are-Are you there?</i>

201
00:11:47.708 --> 00:11:49.667
<i>They're-They're with me.</i>

202
00:11:49.668 --> 00:11:51.920
<i>Hannah? Bailey? Are you all right?</i>

203
00:11:52.546 --> 00:11:55.215
- Charlie? [pants] It's okay.
- <i>Hey...</i>

204
00:11:56.466 --> 00:11:57.634
[door opens]

205
00:11:58.218 --> 00:11:59.802
[Charlie] Bailey!

206
00:11:59.803 --> 00:12:01.220
[both sigh]

207
00:12:01.221 --> 00:12:02.680
- [Charlie] Hannah.
- Hey.

208
00:12:02.681 --> 00:12:05.975
Thank God. I've been so worried.
I tried texting and emailing. but--

209
00:12:05.976 --> 00:12:09.353
Yeah. we've been off e-mail and text.
Are we... Are we okay here?

210
00:12:09.354 --> 00:12:11.314
Yeah. Yes. We've got a ton of security.

211
00:12:11.315 --> 00:12:13.442
How long have you been tailing us?

212
00:12:14.234 --> 00:12:15.776
[Charlie] Since you left LA.

213
00:12:15.777 --> 00:12:16.778
[Hannah] Charlie.

214
00:12:17.404 --> 00:12:18.405
Yeah.

215
00:12:19.823 --> 00:12:21.325
I need you to come with me.

216
00:12:32.211 --> 00:12:33.753
Charlie. what is going on?

217
00:12:33.754 --> 00:12:35.088
Just... Come on.

218
00:12:40.302 --> 00:12:42.179
- Bailey. sweetheart.
- Oh. my God.

219
00:12:42.846 --> 00:12:44.765
Nicholas. what the hell?

220
00:12:45.432 --> 00:12:47.517
- Charlie?
- I couldn't say anything over the phone.

221
00:12:47.518 --> 00:12:49.686
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

222
00:12:50.521 --> 00:12:52.104
We just thought it was for the best.

223
00:12:52.105 --> 00:12:53.689
You thought this was for the best?

224
00:12:53.690 --> 00:12:56.776
People have been chasing us
for the last four days.

225
00:12:56.777 --> 00:12:58.403
And someone tried to kill me. Hannah.

226
00:12:59.613 --> 00:13:00.948
Oh.

227
00:13:01.448 --> 00:13:02.823
What?

228
00:13:02.824 --> 00:13:06.662
He collapsed last week leaving Freddy's.
We thought it was his heart. but...

229
00:13:07.538 --> 00:13:08.829
they did a tox scan.

230
00:13:08.830 --> 00:13:11.123
What. you... [sighs] You were poisoned?

231
00:13:11.124 --> 00:13:12.292
We don't know who.

232
00:13:12.793 --> 00:13:14.920
- We know. Pop.
- No. Jesus. Charlie. we don't.

233
00:13:15.504 --> 00:13:17.505
- There's no proof.
- Come on. Dad.

234
00:13:17.506 --> 00:13:18.881
You think this was the Campanos?

235
00:13:18.882 --> 00:13:21.717
It had to have been. And we had
to let them think they succeeded.

236
00:13:21.718 --> 00:13:23.302
so they didn't try to finish the job.

237
00:13:23.303 --> 00:13:26.305
If it was Frank. though...
Well. when he wants someone dead...

238
00:13:26.306 --> 00:13:30.142
[stammers] Why would he want you dead?
You said you were... you were close.

239
00:13:30.143 --> 00:13:32.937
That he'd never hurt you.
that he'd never hurt us. So why--

240
00:13:32.938 --> 00:13:37.192
Well. there was only one issue that
has ever come between Frank and me.

241
00:13:39.278 --> 00:13:40.279
Owen.

242
00:13:58.672 --> 00:13:59.673
[grunts]

243
00:14:24.531 --> 00:14:25.574
[knocks on door]

244
00:14:26.158 --> 00:14:27.326
Grady?

245
00:14:33.790 --> 00:14:36.125
[soccer commentators chatting]

246
00:14:36.126 --> 00:14:37.211
Grady?

247
00:15:10.619 --> 00:15:12.621
[TV chatter continues]

248
00:15:15.207 --> 00:15:16.375
[Ed] Grady?

249
00:15:19.211 --> 00:15:20.254
Grady?

250
00:15:24.383 --> 00:15:25.466
[sighs]

251
00:15:25.467 --> 00:15:27.261
[knocks on door]

252
00:15:28.178 --> 00:15:30.429
Grady. I need you to come
to the door. Maris sent us.

253
00:15:30.430 --> 00:15:31.974
We've got Austin PD here.

254
00:15:33.058 --> 00:15:34.309
Grady?

255
00:15:37.938 --> 00:15:39.814
Larry. walk around back.

256
00:15:39.815 --> 00:15:43.109
Do a visual inspection. check for
any signs of foul play or forced entry.

257
00:15:43.110 --> 00:15:44.361
You got it.

258
00:15:54.538 --> 00:15:56.748
[Ed] I hear the TV. and his car's here.

259
00:16:00.961 --> 00:16:02.670
[Larry] I see a door open on his balcony.

260
00:16:02.671 --> 00:16:04.589
- [Ed] Does it look like it was forced?
- Yeah. it does.

261
00:16:04.590 --> 00:16:05.883
Okay. we're going in.

262
00:16:13.056 --> 00:16:15.391
- Grady?
- [panting]

263
00:16:15.392 --> 00:16:16.810
Last chance to open up!

264
00:16:17.644 --> 00:16:19.646
[knocking continues]

265
00:16:24.902 --> 00:16:27.613
Oh. no. No. No. no. no.

266
00:16:28.822 --> 00:16:30.657
Grady? Hey.

267
00:16:39.082 --> 00:16:40.291
[Ed] Grady?

268
00:16:40.292 --> 00:16:41.543
Stand back.

269
00:16:42.461 --> 00:16:44.421
When we come in. do not move.

270
00:16:47.132 --> 00:16:49.509
Okay. we're coming in.
Stand back from the door.

271
00:16:49.510 --> 00:16:50.801
All right. guys. Hit it.

272
00:16:50.802 --> 00:16:52.804
[banging]

273
00:16:57.935 --> 00:17:00.437
Owen called me. A year ago.

274
00:17:01.396 --> 00:17:04.315
Said that you weren't safe.
That we had to make a plan.

275
00:17:04.316 --> 00:17:08.861
I told him that we had a plan. that he
should stay away. and I thought he did.

276
00:17:08.862 --> 00:17:11.948
And then a week before this all started.
he calls me again. wanting my help.

277
00:17:11.949 --> 00:17:13.491
Wants me to turn against Frank.

278
00:17:13.492 --> 00:17:15.201
Frank couldn't have known that. could he?

279
00:17:15.202 --> 00:17:16.993
[Nicholas] Frank's people
are sophisticated.

280
00:17:16.994 --> 00:17:18.913
especially when it comes
to protecting their business.

281
00:17:18.914 --> 00:17:21.874
And if Owen set off alarm bells.
they'd be hunting him.

282
00:17:21.875 --> 00:17:24.418
Watching. Maybe tapping our phones.

283
00:17:24.419 --> 00:17:27.046
Right. And that's why
we had to be so careful.

284
00:17:27.047 --> 00:17:28.674
Sure. sure. But...

285
00:17:29.842 --> 00:17:32.677
But I still don't understand.
Why would Frank come after you?

286
00:17:32.678 --> 00:17:34.262
I'm still not convinced he would.

287
00:17:34.263 --> 00:17:35.930
If Frank thought
he was involved with Owen--

288
00:17:35.931 --> 00:17:38.891
Wouldn't he just call you?
If you two were so close--

289
00:17:38.892 --> 00:17:42.563
We are. but there are some lines...
there are some lines that you don't cross.

290
00:17:43.313 --> 00:17:44.438
Owen just thinks he's so smart.

291
00:17:44.439 --> 00:17:47.066
Thinks he can outwit everybody else
with his reckless bullshit.

292
00:17:47.067 --> 00:17:49.652
Never stopping to consider that
if he'ld just leave well enough alone...

293
00:17:49.653 --> 00:17:51.237
- Just stop.
- ...that we'd all be fine.

294
00:17:51.238 --> 00:17:53.030
- safe in our lives. if he'd just...
- Stop.

295
00:17:53.031 --> 00:17:54.490
- ...stay under his fucking rock!
- Nicholas.

296
00:17:54.491 --> 00:17:56.159
Just stop it already!

297
00:17:56.743 --> 00:18:00.121
How can you blame him?
You're the one who works for these people.

298
00:18:00.122 --> 00:18:02.832
You're the one who brought us
into this mess. He tried to get us out.

299
00:18:02.833 --> 00:18:05.126
Oh. Bailey. look.
I have tried to explain--

300
00:18:05.127 --> 00:18:07.044
Oh. no. I can't...
I can't do this right now.

301
00:18:07.045 --> 00:18:08.713
I'm so glad you're alive. I'm so glad.

302
00:18:08.714 --> 00:18:15.303
But I have had the most awful.
bizarre week and I... I just need to...

303
00:18:15.304 --> 00:18:18.264
Bailey and I have been driving all day.
We need a minute.

304
00:18:18.265 --> 00:18:21.559
Maybe some water and a sandwich. Charlie.

305
00:18:21.560 --> 00:18:24.062
Of course. It's the...
You know where the kitchen is.

306
00:18:26.440 --> 00:18:29.026
She loves you. She really does.

307
00:18:31.361 --> 00:18:33.655
But she's also been lied to
her whole life.

308
00:18:36.909 --> 00:18:38.368
Something to consider.

309
00:18:42.998 --> 00:18:46.667
- [police radio chatter]
- [clamoring]

310
00:18:46.668 --> 00:18:49.755
[officer] No. I can't. I need you
to get back in your house. please.

311
00:18:57.095 --> 00:18:58.555
[shutter clicking]

312
00:19:01.433 --> 00:19:02.558
I mean. I knew he drank.

313
00:19:02.559 --> 00:19:04.686
- But I didn't know he was into that shit.
- He wasn't.

314
00:19:31.171 --> 00:19:33.257
You guys check for egress out the window?

315
00:20:05.372 --> 00:20:07.374
- [sighs]
- [engine starts]

316
00:20:11.044 --> 00:20:12.462
- [Bailey sighs]
- [Hannah] You okay?

317
00:20:13.714 --> 00:20:14.756
Uh. yeah.

318
00:20:15.299 --> 00:20:17.217
[breathes shakily] Yeah.

319
00:20:19.678 --> 00:20:22.514
[crying] No. No. sorry.

320
00:20:25.475 --> 00:20:27.144
Don't apologize.

321
00:20:27.895 --> 00:20:30.354
I'm proud of you
for standing up for yourself.

322
00:20:30.355 --> 00:20:32.858
especially with Nicholas. it isn't easy.

323
00:20:33.442 --> 00:20:35.235
[breathes shakily]

324
00:20:36.403 --> 00:20:40.156
What are we gonna do?
I mean. Frank is... is so ruthless.

325
00:20:40.157 --> 00:20:44.577
He tri-tried to kill his best friend
and if... if this is because of Dad. then...

326
00:20:44.578 --> 00:20:46.121
Yeah. [shushes]

327
00:20:47.164 --> 00:20:48.623
Just take a breath.

328
00:20:48.624 --> 00:20:49.707
[breathes shakily]

329
00:20:49.708 --> 00:20:53.045
[sighs] We're just gonna take it
one thing at a time. okay?

330
00:21:06.141 --> 00:21:07.683
[phone buzzes]

331
00:21:07.684 --> 00:21:10.187
[sighs] Would you pass the naan please?

332
00:21:24.535 --> 00:21:26.954
- What?
- [Charlie] Everything okay?

333
00:21:27.496 --> 00:21:28.497
I'm gonna get some water.

334
00:21:37.506 --> 00:21:40.299
[breathing heavily]

335
00:21:40.300 --> 00:21:41.592
- Come on.
- [line ringing]

336
00:21:41.593 --> 00:21:44.012
Just please pick up. Pick up.

337
00:21:44.596 --> 00:21:45.930
[sighs] Owen. pick up.

338
00:21:45.931 --> 00:21:47.890
[electronic voice] <i>The person you are
trying to reach is unavailable.</i>

339
00:21:47.891 --> 00:21:49.559
<i>Please leave a message after the--</i>

340
00:21:49.560 --> 00:21:50.561
Fuck.

341
00:21:57.067 --> 00:21:58.569
You took all the evidence?

342
00:21:59.862 --> 00:22:01.279
Yeah. yeah.

343
00:22:01.280 --> 00:22:02.614
House is clean.

344
00:22:03.615 --> 00:22:04.992
Any sign of the two women?

345
00:22:06.076 --> 00:22:08.495
Well. not since...

346
00:22:09.329 --> 00:22:11.080
No idea who coldcocked you?

347
00:22:11.081 --> 00:22:12.875
I never saw her before.

348
00:22:15.335 --> 00:22:16.461
Maybe they hired protection.

349
00:22:19.923 --> 00:22:21.550
Word's out to everyone in town.

350
00:22:22.551 --> 00:22:25.053
Hey. our friend in the Marshal's office
is on it too.

351
00:22:25.971 --> 00:22:28.264
If the two women are still in Austin.
we'll find them.

352
00:22:28.265 --> 00:22:29.600
The sooner. the better.

353
00:22:31.560 --> 00:22:32.894
You want me to update Frank?

354
00:22:32.895 --> 00:22:35.147
You don't think
I talk to my own fucking father?

355
00:22:38.358 --> 00:22:39.818
Go do your job.

356
00:22:44.281 --> 00:22:46.700
[crying]

357
00:23:03.091 --> 00:23:04.301
[sighs]

358
00:23:12.017 --> 00:23:13.976
- Are you okay?
- [Hannah] Yeah.

359
00:23:13.977 --> 00:23:16.896
Hey. when is the last time
you saw him? Frank?

360
00:23:16.897 --> 00:23:18.023
Last week.

361
00:23:18.690 --> 00:23:20.191
After the party. we had lunch.

362
00:23:20.192 --> 00:23:21.567
Did he ask you about Owen?

363
00:23:21.568 --> 00:23:22.694
No.

364
00:23:23.320 --> 00:23:25.947
[Hannah] You work for him for 40 years.

365
00:23:25.948 --> 00:23:27.574
go to prison for him...

366
00:23:29.159 --> 00:23:31.160
And then
without so much as a conversation.

367
00:23:31.161 --> 00:23:34.455
he poisons you on a hunch
that you might be in cahoots

368
00:23:34.456 --> 00:23:37.834
with your son-in-law
that he knows you hate.

369
00:23:37.835 --> 00:23:40.670
This is what I've been struggling with.
Frank is ruthless. but--

370
00:23:40.671 --> 00:23:43.005
But something's not adding up.

371
00:23:43.006 --> 00:23:44.507
No. not exactly.

372
00:23:44.508 --> 00:23:46.510
Is there anyone else
who might wanna kill you?

373
00:23:47.135 --> 00:23:49.220
Well... [stammers] ...you have represented

374
00:23:49.221 --> 00:23:50.930
some of the biggest criminals
in the country.

375
00:23:50.931 --> 00:23:53.599
- Yes. and they're in my debt.
- Yeah. so is Frank.

376
00:23:53.600 --> 00:23:55.560
- Well...
- I'm just saying...

377
00:23:55.561 --> 00:23:58.605
[stammers] ...someone should have
a conversation with him.

378
00:23:59.189 --> 00:24:01.482
No. that is too dangerous.

379
00:24:01.483 --> 00:24:04.777
No. if Frank wants me dead.
letting him know I'm alive...

380
00:24:04.778 --> 00:24:06.529
I wasn't suggesting that it'd be you.

381
00:24:06.530 --> 00:24:08.698
Hannah. his men have been
chasing you for days.

382
00:24:08.699 --> 00:24:10.825
I'm not gonna waltz
into the Campano headquarters.

383
00:24:10.826 --> 00:24:15.204
but if we surprise him somewhere alone.
on our territory. Somewhere safe.

384
00:24:15.205 --> 00:24:17.665
You go to Frank. He doesn't come to you.

385
00:24:17.666 --> 00:24:19.208
He came to your birthday party.

386
00:24:19.209 --> 00:24:21.460
Well. it's not like
we can have another one of those.

387
00:24:21.461 --> 00:24:22.962
We can have a memorial.

388
00:24:22.963 --> 00:24:25.256
- Oh. Jesus Christ.
- It was your idea to play dead.

389
00:24:25.257 --> 00:24:28.176
We do something small.
Just here at The Never Dry.

390
00:24:28.177 --> 00:24:32.138
This weekend.
Nothing fancy. with your inner circle.

391
00:24:32.139 --> 00:24:34.223
without drawing attention.

392
00:24:34.224 --> 00:24:36.726
We invite a few cops to be safe.

393
00:24:36.727 --> 00:24:40.355
- Lieutenant Smuts and some prosecutors.
- Yeah. Frank wouldn't see us coming.

394
00:24:40.939 --> 00:24:43.107
We can call it a wake
if it'll make you feel better.

395
00:24:43.108 --> 00:24:45.193
None of this is gonna make me feel better.

396
00:24:45.194 --> 00:24:47.528
Then maybe you should think about
someone other than yourself.

397
00:24:47.529 --> 00:24:48.697
[stammers]

398
00:24:53.452 --> 00:24:56.705
We need to talk to him.
We need to figure out what's going on.

399
00:24:57.331 --> 00:24:58.999
All right. Well. you know what I need?

400
00:25:00.792 --> 00:25:02.376
I need a drink.

401
00:25:02.377 --> 00:25:04.171
- Hey. you want me to fix you--
- I do not.

402
00:25:06.215 --> 00:25:07.966
I can find my own way to the bar.

403
00:25:25.943 --> 00:25:27.402
[Hannah] I love this bar.

404
00:25:28.529 --> 00:25:30.154
I think I love it for the name alone.

405
00:25:30.155 --> 00:25:32.991
But when you add in the history.

406
00:25:33.992 --> 00:25:36.494
- it's pretty cool.
- Are you trying to soften me up?

407
00:25:36.495 --> 00:25:39.414
I would've sent Bailey
if I was trying to do that.

408
00:25:44.837 --> 00:25:47.046
I thought I'd gotten her back for good.

409
00:25:47.047 --> 00:25:48.674
I thought this was all over.

410
00:25:51.343 --> 00:25:54.096
It's all I've been able
to think about the last four days. is...

411
00:25:56.306 --> 00:25:57.808
how to keep her safe.

412
00:26:00.853 --> 00:26:01.895
[Hannah] Yes. please.

413
00:26:03.021 --> 00:26:04.273
[Nicholas] It's what I do.

414
00:26:05.023 --> 00:26:06.525
I take care of things.

415
00:26:10.028 --> 00:26:11.113
But this...

416
00:26:12.614 --> 00:26:15.158
But this. I don't have a single idea.

417
00:26:16.702 --> 00:26:19.871
Other than taking out my shotgun.
hunting down Owen. and. uh...

418
00:26:19.872 --> 00:26:20.873
Mmm...

419
00:26:21.415 --> 00:26:24.083
That's not the answer. [clears throat]

420
00:26:24.084 --> 00:26:25.544
Says his wife.

421
00:26:28.046 --> 00:26:30.299
He's not high on my list either right now.

422
00:26:32.509 --> 00:26:35.553
But he's her father and she needs him.

423
00:26:35.554 --> 00:26:37.513
Safe and alive.

424
00:26:37.514 --> 00:26:39.558
Preferably part of her life.

425
00:26:41.643 --> 00:26:43.478
You know that last one isn't possible.

426
00:26:44.563 --> 00:26:46.981
It's definitely not possible
if we don't talk to Frank.

427
00:26:46.982 --> 00:26:48.775
You gonna ask him if he killed me?

428
00:26:49.276 --> 00:26:53.655
Not in so many words. no.
But I am pretty good at reading people.

429
00:26:54.448 --> 00:27:01.371
And I am pretty good at convincing people
to be their most reasonable selves.

430
00:27:05.792 --> 00:27:06.835
[inhales deeply]

431
00:27:16.929 --> 00:27:18.138
[Bailey] You convinced him?

432
00:27:19.181 --> 00:27:20.264
Looks that way.

433
00:27:20.265 --> 00:27:24.310
What if Frank is behind this? [stammers]
What are you gonna say to him?

434
00:27:24.311 --> 00:27:25.312
[Hannah] I don't know.

435
00:27:25.896 --> 00:27:28.898
But we need this to stop
before someone else gets hurt.

436
00:27:28.899 --> 00:27:31.276
[sighs]

437
00:27:33.403 --> 00:27:34.404
Grady's dead.

438
00:27:35.989 --> 00:27:36.990
What?

439
00:27:38.158 --> 00:27:39.368
Oh. my God.

440
00:27:40.536 --> 00:27:42.745
Does Dad know?
[stammers] Because if they find him--

441
00:27:42.746 --> 00:27:44.789
- They are not gonna find him.
- But if they...

442
00:27:44.790 --> 00:27:48.084
[breathes shakily] God.
if they killed Grady... [stammers]

443
00:27:48.085 --> 00:27:51.003
If Grandpa's right a-and
this is because of what Dad was doing--

444
00:27:51.004 --> 00:27:54.131
Then I'm gonna make it clear to Frank that
you and I had nothing to do with this.

445
00:27:54.132 --> 00:27:56.218
that your dad was just trying
to protect us.

446
00:27:56.718 --> 00:28:00.346
And that if Frank guarantees our safety.
he'll stop.

447
00:28:00.347 --> 00:28:02.224
And we can go back to the way things were.

448
00:28:05.769 --> 00:28:07.271
We can't risk him coming here.

449
00:28:09.147 --> 00:28:10.274
Is... [scoffs]

450
00:28:11.149 --> 00:28:13.986
So that's
our best case scenario. isn't it?

451
00:28:14.695 --> 00:28:17.114
No. No. it isn't.

452
00:28:17.990 --> 00:28:20.408
But unless
we can stop running and breathe.

453
00:28:20.409 --> 00:28:22.035
we're never gonna figure the rest out.

454
00:28:24.413 --> 00:28:27.499
Get packed. We're staying
at the Sanctuary for a few days.

455
00:29:42.241 --> 00:29:44.243
[crickets chirping]

456
00:30:29.037 --> 00:30:30.289
[Charlie] Bailey.

457
00:30:31.999 --> 00:30:33.584
I thought I heard someone in here.

458
00:30:38.505 --> 00:30:40.549
My mom took these. didn't she?

459
00:30:41.049 --> 00:30:42.676
Oh. yeah.

460
00:30:44.469 --> 00:30:46.471
Man. I loved these.

461
00:30:47.848 --> 00:30:49.933
[sighs] She had a real eye.

462
00:30:51.435 --> 00:30:52.852
Where'd you find them?

463
00:30:52.853 --> 00:30:54.229
In the back of that frame.

464
00:30:54.938 --> 00:30:56.440
Yeah. [chuckles]

465
00:30:57.107 --> 00:30:58.984
My dad never got how cool they were.

466
00:31:00.360 --> 00:31:01.528
You should take them.

467
00:31:02.029 --> 00:31:03.362
Really?

468
00:31:03.363 --> 00:31:04.489
He won't notice.

469
00:31:10.120 --> 00:31:11.205
How you doing?

470
00:31:12.623 --> 00:31:15.000
All this history and anger. I. um...

471
00:31:16.001 --> 00:31:19.087
So weird. 'cause it kind of has
nothing to do with me. But. um...

472
00:31:20.589 --> 00:31:21.965
I'm so caught up in it.

473
00:31:22.674 --> 00:31:23.675
[Charlie] Yeah.

474
00:31:24.343 --> 00:31:28.054
It's kind of amazing you haven't
cut us all off and run away to Scotland.

475
00:31:28.055 --> 00:31:29.680
[Bailey chuckles]

476
00:31:29.681 --> 00:31:31.475
I'd pick somewhere
way further than Scotland.

477
00:31:32.559 --> 00:31:33.644
[chuckles]

478
00:31:48.116 --> 00:31:49.535
[Charlie] She'd be proud of you.

479
00:31:50.744 --> 00:31:52.829
She'd be upset
at what you've had to go through.

480
00:31:53.789 --> 00:31:54.790
But

481
00:31:56.583 --> 00:31:58.085
she'd be really proud.

482
00:32:06.385 --> 00:32:08.886
Austin PD says
they're not going to investigate.

483
00:32:08.887 --> 00:32:10.847
They're ruling it
an accidental overdose. but--

484
00:32:10.848 --> 00:32:12.390
- Yeah. I know.
- [Rochelle] <i>Hey.</i>

485
00:32:12.391 --> 00:32:14.476
<i>I've got an Owen Michaels
who wants to talk to you.</i>

486
00:32:21.400 --> 00:32:22.442
Maris Anderson.

487
00:32:22.943 --> 00:32:25.112
[on phone]
<i>Grady's death wasn't an accident.</i>

488
00:32:25.779 --> 00:32:27.530
Is this Ethan Young?

489
00:32:27.531 --> 00:32:29.491
<i>Listen to me.
you guys need to look into this.</i>

490
00:32:30.033 --> 00:32:32.493
You're in a position
to be telling me how to do my job?

491
00:32:32.494 --> 00:32:35.496
- Have you been to his storage unit?
- Excuse me?

492
00:32:35.497 --> 00:32:38.583
<i>Grady had a storage unit in San Marcos.</i>

493
00:32:38.584 --> 00:32:40.251
<i>They cleaned it out. Left his badge.</i>

494
00:32:40.252 --> 00:32:43.504
<i>You should send a forensic team over.
You need an address?</i>

495
00:32:43.505 --> 00:32:45.047
I know the place. I'll get a warrant.

496
00:32:45.048 --> 00:32:46.049
Go.

497
00:32:46.675 --> 00:32:48.968
- [phone clicks]
- I got it covered.

498
00:32:48.969 --> 00:32:51.513
Well. if you had it covered.
you would've already been there.

499
00:32:55.475 --> 00:32:58.895
I'm guessing you pulled Grady into
this little side pocket investigation.

500
00:32:58.896 --> 00:33:01.772
So I don't really feel like
you should be placing blame at our feet.

501
00:33:01.773 --> 00:33:04.609
But if you sincerely wanna help. maybe
you should come down and talk to us.

502
00:33:04.610 --> 00:33:05.652
I've got some questions.

503
00:33:06.445 --> 00:33:07.612
Yeah. that's not gonna happen.

504
00:33:07.613 --> 00:33:10.198
Would you rather
I send a homicide detective your way?

505
00:33:10.199 --> 00:33:12.366
I had nothing to do with this.
you know that.

506
00:33:12.367 --> 00:33:15.328
- Do I?
- Grady didn't OD. he was killed!

507
00:33:15.329 --> 00:33:17.664
- Just go to the storage center.
- [phone clacks]

508
00:33:21.585 --> 00:33:23.212
[device beeping]

509
00:33:33.597 --> 00:33:35.598
No. no. no. no. no. no. no.

510
00:33:35.599 --> 00:33:38.267
[Nicholas] <i>Seth is on alert.
There's security in the bar.</i>

511
00:33:38.268 --> 00:33:40.144
And you get ten minutes.

512
00:33:40.145 --> 00:33:42.230
We meet you at the back door.
we get you both out--

513
00:33:42.231 --> 00:33:43.273
Nicholas.

514
00:33:43.857 --> 00:33:46.192
We've been through this twice now.
We're good.

515
00:33:46.193 --> 00:33:47.528
Guests are starting to arrive.

516
00:33:53.450 --> 00:33:55.035
Be careful. will you?

517
00:33:56.453 --> 00:33:57.871
You're starting to sound like me.

518
00:34:06.630 --> 00:34:08.047
She is something.

519
00:34:10.050 --> 00:34:11.260
She's the best.

520
00:34:15.472 --> 00:34:17.390
Look. you. um...

521
00:34:17.391 --> 00:34:19.893
You should know that I-I-I...

522
00:34:20.811 --> 00:34:22.020
I had no intention...

523
00:34:23.522 --> 00:34:25.315
I mean. I feel badly

524
00:34:26.859 --> 00:34:29.068
that you. well--

525
00:34:29.069 --> 00:34:30.736
Are you trying to apologize?

526
00:34:30.737 --> 00:34:33.657
I just. I didn't... [sighs]

527
00:34:34.283 --> 00:34:36.534
I didn't know that
you would take it so hard.

528
00:34:39.246 --> 00:34:40.414
[Bailey] It's okay.

529
00:34:41.290 --> 00:34:42.540
Really. it's...

530
00:34:42.541 --> 00:34:43.542
[inhales sharply]

531
00:34:44.418 --> 00:34:46.419
[clicks tongue] Just. uh...

532
00:34:46.420 --> 00:34:47.880
try not to do it again.

533
00:34:53.886 --> 00:34:55.512
[Teddy] You sure this is a good idea?

534
00:34:56.096 --> 00:34:59.724
I'll be fine. But you seem a little antsy.

535
00:34:59.725 --> 00:35:00.893
I'm good. Pop.

536
00:35:01.602 --> 00:35:02.603
I'm good.

537
00:35:03.103 --> 00:35:05.189
And you've got enough on your mind.

538
00:35:08.275 --> 00:35:09.902
You want me to come inside?

539
00:35:11.403 --> 00:35:12.738
He was my friend.

540
00:35:13.447 --> 00:35:14.615
not yours.

541
00:35:16.992 --> 00:35:18.410
[door opens]

542
00:35:33.342 --> 00:35:35.218
[people chattering]

543
00:35:35.219 --> 00:35:38.680
["Down There By The Train" playing]

544
00:35:43.393 --> 00:35:45.103
Thanks for coming. guys.

545
00:35:46.021 --> 00:35:48.524
Lieutenant. thanks for coming
on such short notice.

546
00:35:58.367 --> 00:35:59.409
Frank.

547
00:35:59.910 --> 00:36:00.994
Charlie.

548
00:36:07.835 --> 00:36:08.919
I'm sorry.

549
00:36:10.504 --> 00:36:11.672
I should've reached out.

550
00:36:12.381 --> 00:36:13.756
Hit me pretty hard.

551
00:36:13.757 --> 00:36:15.884
[Charlie] It hit all of us pretty hard.

552
00:36:19.263 --> 00:36:20.848
Frank. do you know. um...

553
00:36:21.598 --> 00:36:22.766
Hannah Hall.

554
00:36:24.226 --> 00:36:27.270
Hannah's family. Frank. She was Owen's...
Um. I mean. Ethan's...

555
00:36:27.271 --> 00:36:28.897
I know who she is.

556
00:36:34.486 --> 00:36:35.779
[sighs]

557
00:36:36.572 --> 00:36:37.697
We need to get you out of here.

558
00:36:37.698 --> 00:36:39.740
- He makes one call to Teddy--
- No. He won't.

559
00:36:39.741 --> 00:36:41.200
- Hannah.
- He won't.

560
00:36:41.201 --> 00:36:44.705
I need to try. Charlie. please.

561
00:36:48.458 --> 00:36:49.459
Okay.

562
00:36:50.085 --> 00:36:52.004
All right. Ten minutes.

563
00:37:01.013 --> 00:37:02.306
[Bailey] He's here?

564
00:37:03.849 --> 00:37:04.933
Yeah.

565
00:37:06.727 --> 00:37:07.936
Ten minutes.

566
00:37:08.729 --> 00:37:10.271
[Bailey] What's Frank like?

567
00:37:10.272 --> 00:37:13.233
I-I met Quinn. I... [sighs] I liked her.

568
00:37:14.401 --> 00:37:15.861
He can't be all bad.

569
00:37:17.571 --> 00:37:19.031
Nobody's all bad.

570
00:37:20.991 --> 00:37:23.994
Okay. so... What's he like?

571
00:37:25.579 --> 00:37:27.288
Well. he's quick.

572
00:37:27.289 --> 00:37:29.832
Explain something to him once.
he's got it.

573
00:37:29.833 --> 00:37:31.251
Didn't go to college.

574
00:37:31.835 --> 00:37:33.754
But he's as bright as anybody I ever met.

575
00:37:34.588 --> 00:37:36.507
He's got a wicked sense of humor.

576
00:37:37.132 --> 00:37:39.009
He sounds fun. [chuckles]

577
00:37:40.093 --> 00:37:41.595
Most dangerous people.

578
00:37:43.305 --> 00:37:44.598
they are.

579
00:37:46.433 --> 00:37:49.853
["Down There By The Train"
continues playing]

580
00:37:57.569 --> 00:37:58.904
Mind if I sit?

581
00:38:07.246 --> 00:38:08.330
Nicholas was family.

582
00:38:08.914 --> 00:38:10.414
Yeah. we were family too.

583
00:38:10.415 --> 00:38:11.667
[scoffs]

584
00:38:13.502 --> 00:38:14.586
No offense.

585
00:38:15.379 --> 00:38:16.588
hardly the same.

586
00:38:19.383 --> 00:38:21.552
I knew Nicky for 40 years.

587
00:38:22.135 --> 00:38:23.928
- Our kids grew up together.
- Mmm.

588
00:38:23.929 --> 00:38:25.013
Thick as thieves.

589
00:38:25.889 --> 00:38:27.056
Until they weren't.

590
00:38:27.057 --> 00:38:28.558
[chuckles]

591
00:38:28.559 --> 00:38:30.936
Miss Hall. what are you trying to say?
Come on. spit it out. Come on.

592
00:38:33.647 --> 00:38:35.148
Mr. Campano.

593
00:38:35.983 --> 00:38:39.820
we need to talk about my situation.
mine and Bailey's.

594
00:38:41.530 --> 00:38:43.198
I've just lost a friend.

595
00:38:44.783 --> 00:38:45.993
And I am...

596
00:38:47.578 --> 00:38:50.580
not interested in negotiating
at this time.

597
00:38:50.581 --> 00:38:53.124
[sighs] I'm not interested
in negotiating either.

598
00:38:53.125 --> 00:38:55.126
But ever since Nicholas was killed...

599
00:38:55.127 --> 00:38:57.629
- What did you say?
- ...Bailey and I have been on the run.

600
00:38:58.630 --> 00:39:01.884
Did you say...
Did you say Nicholas was killed?

601
00:39:02.467 --> 00:39:04.261
What exactly are you playing at?

602
00:39:05.012 --> 00:39:06.763
I'm not playing at anything.

603
00:39:09.433 --> 00:39:10.893
Nicholas was poisoned.

604
00:39:13.228 --> 00:39:14.645
Everything okay over here?

605
00:39:14.646 --> 00:39:16.272
[Frank] No. it's fucking not.

606
00:39:16.273 --> 00:39:18.065
She's saying someone killed your father.

607
00:39:18.066 --> 00:39:19.276
It's true. Frank.

608
00:39:20.652 --> 00:39:21.653
[sighs]

609
00:39:22.154 --> 00:39:24.531
There was poison on the toxicology report.

610
00:39:25.115 --> 00:39:28.577
[Frank] I want to see that report.
find out who did it.

611
00:39:29.161 --> 00:39:30.746
And when I find them.

612
00:39:31.872 --> 00:39:33.916
I'll rip their fucking throat out.

613
00:39:37.503 --> 00:39:38.711
He said that?

614
00:39:38.712 --> 00:39:40.839
He... He wasn't faking it. Pop.

615
00:39:41.632 --> 00:39:44.175
- All right. Well. I need to talk to him.
- Grandpa--

616
00:39:44.176 --> 00:39:47.094
No. If Frank didn't do this.
we need to figure out who the hell did.

617
00:39:47.095 --> 00:39:48.430
Get him up here.

618
00:39:56.855 --> 00:39:59.482
- [buttons click]
- [line ringing]

619
00:39:59.483 --> 00:40:01.485
[phone ringing]

620
00:40:05.239 --> 00:40:07.156
- This is Charlie.
- <i>It's Ethan.</i>

621
00:40:07.157 --> 00:40:09.493
What the fuck is happening?
Are they there?

622
00:40:11.578 --> 00:40:14.831
Yeah. I'm sorry.
We are closed for a private family event.

623
00:40:16.583 --> 00:40:18.335
- [phone beeps]
- [sighs]

624
00:40:22.589 --> 00:40:25.217
How could you think
I would do such a thing to you?

625
00:40:25.926 --> 00:40:30.137
I didn't want to. But who else would have
the motive. or the guts?

626
00:40:30.138 --> 00:40:33.559
If I thought you were helping Ethan.
I'd have paid you a visit.

627
00:40:34.726 --> 00:40:36.687
Not sent a fucking assassin.

628
00:40:37.521 --> 00:40:39.063
Jesus. Nicky. who do you think I am?

629
00:40:39.064 --> 00:40:41.107
Maybe the guy
who went after his granddaughter

630
00:40:41.108 --> 00:40:42.818
as soon as he was out of the picture.

631
00:40:44.570 --> 00:40:46.655
Teddy said Ethan's been after us
for months.

632
00:40:47.281 --> 00:40:50.200
- We had a deal.
- We had a deal when you were alive.

633
00:40:51.743 --> 00:40:52.911
And when you weren't.

634
00:40:54.079 --> 00:40:55.371
Teddy said we had a problem.

635
00:40:55.372 --> 00:40:56.623
So Teddy was driving this?

636
00:40:58.458 --> 00:40:59.751
I make the decisions.

637
00:41:01.587 --> 00:41:03.046
But Teddy runs your day-to-day.

638
00:41:03.630 --> 00:41:06.132
If he wanted to go after Owen.
and Nicholas was in the way--

639
00:41:06.133 --> 00:41:09.719
No one in my employ would lift a finger
without my say so.

640
00:41:09.720 --> 00:41:11.095
[Nicholas] Oh. come on. Frank.

641
00:41:11.096 --> 00:41:13.473
You know that
Teddy's always had a mind of his own.

642
00:41:17.019 --> 00:41:19.271
Yeah. I'm done here.

643
00:41:22.024 --> 00:41:23.901
Is he wrong. Mr. Campano?

644
00:41:25.485 --> 00:41:26.695
What the fuck is this?

645
00:41:27.404 --> 00:41:28.447
Huh. Nicky?

646
00:41:29.281 --> 00:41:31.200
Did Ethan get to you?

647
00:41:32.034 --> 00:41:33.452
No. Ethan called me.

648
00:41:34.494 --> 00:41:35.579
[Frank] Why?

649
00:41:36.246 --> 00:41:37.581
[Nicholas] Ranting and raving.

650
00:41:38.207 --> 00:41:40.625
I told him to stop it.
I haven't seen him in 18 years.

651
00:41:40.626 --> 00:41:43.712
And if I had. I would've
turned him in to you personally.

652
00:41:45.297 --> 00:41:48.717
Then we're in agreement.
and he's still a dead man.

653
00:41:50.052 --> 00:41:51.595
- [Nicholas] All right. fine.
- [gasps]

654
00:41:52.137 --> 00:41:53.554
Fine.

655
00:41:53.555 --> 00:41:56.808
But you and Teddy. you need
to leave the rest of my family alone.

656
00:42:03.398 --> 00:42:06.485
I would never touch your granddaughter.

657
00:42:09.988 --> 00:42:12.407
This one. I can't make any promises.

658
00:42:16.912 --> 00:42:19.373
And you will stay dead.

659
00:42:20.374 --> 00:42:22.459
so they don't try to finish the job.

660
00:42:29.633 --> 00:42:30.717
[door closes]

661
00:42:33.220 --> 00:42:34.847
You were in there for a while.

662
00:42:35.556 --> 00:42:37.140
It's a lot to digest.

663
00:42:38.642 --> 00:42:39.852
Is everything okay?

664
00:42:42.479 --> 00:42:44.147
Get me the fuck outta here. Teddy.

665
00:42:56.243 --> 00:42:57.952
Nicholas. why?

666
00:42:57.953 --> 00:42:59.453
Why would you promise him Owen?

667
00:42:59.454 --> 00:43:02.498
I don't know why you're upset.
He guaranteed your safety.

668
00:43:02.499 --> 00:43:04.167
He didn't guarantee Hannah's safety.

669
00:43:04.168 --> 00:43:06.586
That's just him talking. I know Frank.

670
00:43:06.587 --> 00:43:09.088
[Hannah] Twelve hours ago.
you thought maybe he tried to kill you.

671
00:43:09.089 --> 00:43:10.882
And now you two are
on the same wavelength?

672
00:43:10.883 --> 00:43:12.967
All right. you're upset about Owen.
I understand.

673
00:43:12.968 --> 00:43:14.887
But that was the only deal to be made.

674
00:43:15.387 --> 00:43:16.930
[door opens. creaks]

675
00:43:18.390 --> 00:43:20.391
- [bodyguard] Gun!
- [Hannah] Owen!

676
00:43:20.392 --> 00:43:21.726
[Bailey] Leave him alone!

677
00:43:21.727 --> 00:43:24.145
- Get the fuck away from me!
- [Bailey] Stop! Stop it!

678
00:43:24.146 --> 00:43:25.938
- [grunting]
- [pants]

679
00:43:25.939 --> 00:43:27.941
[breathing heavily]

679
00:43:28.305 --> 00:44:28.557
